
Openbox is a → Linux/X#x-window-manager[window manager].

{ Configuration

  • → Linux/X/Openbox/configuration/rc_xml
  • menu.xml
  • autostart
  • environment

  Apparently, openbox can be configured with *ObConf* (the Openbox Configurator Manager)

}
{ TODO

 { Keyboard binding

  → http://openbox.org/wiki/Help:DefaultConfiguration[Some default key bindings]. Cool is:
    • Windows F1 … F4 : goes to nth *desktop* instantly
    • Ctrl+Alt+{left|right}: go to next left/right *desktop*
    • Shift+Alt+{left|right}: almost same thing
    • Alt+Left Mouse Button: Move window
    • Alt+Right Mouse Button: Move border closest to mouse pointer of window beneath mouse.

    Apparently, these can be configured in the `<keyboard>` section in the → Linux/X/Openbox/configuration/rc_xml file.

  }
